What to Expect From Our Attorneys

If you choose Farah & Farah, our promise to you is that we will take care of every aspect of your case. All you need to do is focus on your treatment and getting better. Our expert team of attorneys and staff will:

  • Meet you at your convenience, even after office hours and on weekends.
  • Help find a doctor to properly treat and document your injury.
  • Handle property damage for free.
  • Help obtain a rental vehicle if yours was damaged in an accident.
  • Gather evidence by performing a comprehensive investigation of the incident.
  • Keep you consistently updated on the status of your case.
  • Hire the experts needed in your case, no matter the cost.
  • Negotiate medical bills, so you take home more money when we win your case.
  • Handle all paperwork from insurance companies and medical providers.
  • Fight for the maximum possible verdict or settlement without charging you a dime unless we win.

WE TAKE THE FINANCIAL RISK, NOT YOU

If we don’t win your case, you don’t owe us a cent.

Get to Know Us Better

We are a client-centric injury law firm that has been protecting Florida and Georgia families since 1979. Our law firm was founded by Eddie Farah and built with the help of his brother, Chuck Farah. We wanted to start a law firm that serves clients in a family-like atmosphere.

We started as a small personal injury law office in downtown Jacksonville. During the last 45 years, we have grown to become one of Florida’s largest, most respected personal injury law firms and developed a prominent presence in Georgia. Our growth is fueled by the more than $2 billion in case results we have obtained for our clients.

Our results are no accident. Caring, understanding, and hard work are how we win. We have never wavered from our commitment to putting clients first and treating each one like family.

Our law firm is rooted in family. Eddie Farah has three children who work as attorneys with our firm. Meanwhile, Chuck Farah’s son is attending law school and intends to join our firm. We understand how important your family is to you and how much the whole family suffers when one member is severely injured.

A Team Approach

When we take on your injury case, you will get a team of attorneys, paralegals, and support staff who will combine their resources and strengths to formulate the most effective strategy and win you the highest compensation available. We have found that collaboration yields better results than competition between lawyers.

An Open-Door Policy

We are committed to being available to our clients whenever they need us. We understand that your needs don’t just occur on a nine-to-five schedule. You will always be able to reach your legal team, even if you need us after office hours or during weekends and holidays.

Big Firm Results with a Small Firm Feel

No matter where you are injured in Florida or Georgia, you will find a friendly local Farah & Farah law office where we will treat you like family. Whether you need a personal injury lawyer in Fort Myers, Daytona Beach, Atlanta, or anywhere in between, you can count on a friendly nearby Farah & Farah law office to be there when you need us.

All of our local attorneys have access to the resources of our large firm, so they have the financial backing to go against large corporations and win. This gives our clients the best of both worlds: the personalized representation of a small, friendly office with the case results you would expect from a large law firm.

Call (855) 914-4745 today for a free and confidential consultation.

OUR HOMETOWN OFFICE

Jacksonville

Our founders were born and raised in Jacksonville, and they raised their families here. Starting Farah & Farah in the River City was a natural way for them to give back to the community they felt had given them so much. 

Eddie and Chuck Farah started the Jacksonville personal injury law firm in 1979 with a vision to help accident victims recover while providing a family-like environment and putting their needs first. More than 44 years later, our dedicated personal injury lawyers remain steadfast in carrying out that vision, and not just inside the confines of our Jacksonville personal injury law office. 

While winning outstanding results for injured accident victims will always be our primary focus, we are also committed to doing what we can to prevent accidents. We have seen a dramatic rise in car accidents, motorcycle accidents, and truck accidents in Jacksonville, especially on Interstate 95. 

Drunk driving is a major cause of fatal accidents. This is why we have given away almost 12,315 rides through our Safe Ride program, which provides free vouchers for Uber and similar services during holidays and events when celebrations commonly involve drinking. We have also given away more than 750 free bicycle helmets for kids.  

Jacksonville is our home. These are just examples of the myriad of ways we give back to the people in our community as a firm. Our caring and dedicated attorneys also support local causes on their own through volunteerism and financial giving, which we encourage.

In addition to community service, we take pride in our sponsorships in the area. Farah & Farah is the exclusive injury law firm of the Jacksonville Jaguars, and we work together to connect the Jacksonville community. Some of our sponsorships include:

The Hunt: A season-long documentary series giving Jaguars fans behind-the-scenes access.

Girls Flag Football Player & Coach of the Week: Each winning player/coach will receive a $1,000 grant presented by the Jaguars and Farah & Farah.

Our Jacksonville Personal Injury Lawyers Are Here to Serve All of Your Personal Injury Needs

Our personal injury lawyers in Jacksonville come from diverse backgrounds and accept all types of cases. Some of our attorneys have previous experience defending insurance companies, which gives them an insider’s perspective when handling claims on behalf of injured accident victims.  

Some have worked as prosecutors in the state attorney’s office, giving them valuable experience as trial attorneys. Personal injury lawyers who are adept in trials pose a threat to insurance companies who don’t want to pay, making it easier to win substantial compensation during settlement negotiations.

OFFICE SPOTLIGHT

Our Tampa, FL Office

5100 W. Kennedy Blvd. Suite 250 Tampa, FL 33609
(813) 358-0490

Tampa is Florida’s third-largest city, with three major interstate highways crossing city limits. Also known as “Guava City”, Tampa’s perfect weather is ideal for walking, bicycling, and riding a motorcycle. 

However, these conveniences pose numerous hidden dangers. In 2023 alone, 27,469 car accidents occurred in Hillsborough County, including 216 fatal crashes. Narrow streets, confusing intersections, and frequent left turns make Tampa especially hazardous for vulnerable roadway users such as pedestrians, bicyclists, and motorcycle riders.

Truck drivers heading to and from the port are hurried and impatient because of their tight schedules. Impatient commuters also abound during rush hour on the downtown streets and Interstates 4, 75, and 275. Tourists unfamiliar with the area mingle with these drivers, and many are distracted by their cell phones, and navigation systems.

Our Tampa personal injury lawyers understand Tampa’s legal climate and unique culture. If you have been injured in any type of accident in the Tampa Bay Area, we are here for you.
